<br>
I've said it many times before that the current rate, frankly, sucks. It's very frustrating to gain a level and have your spells out of reach. Verging on level 62, I've gotten exactly one ethereal parchment. Seen a few drop, but lost the roll on'em (don't mind that too much, everyone needs spells and thankfully the groups I've joined don't have melee rolling on parchments, though there's some who think they ought to be able to).<br>
<br>
As for getting my spells ? There's only been a couple I did not have ready to scribe the moment I dinged, aside ancients, and only one I am still missing. Took me a bit to find copies of Burnout IV and Muzzle of Mardu (well, for prices I could stomach anyways). Only spell I am missing up to 60 (aside ancients), is Transon's Elemental Renewal (which I guess is so rare, even the guilds who knock off the Luclin bosses regularly don't get spare copies). So no, I don't think it's unreasonable to expect most of my spells being available to me when I level. Spells are the tools of our trade, and the defining spells of a class should never be that hard to obtain.<br>
