<br>
That is happening already, the trickle effect has kicked in.  Yesterday I saw 2 lvl 61 mage spells for sale in the Bazaar.  Elemental Barrier for 4k (well overpriced for what it is IMO) and Ward of Xegony for 14k.  I bought the pet without blinking and consider it money well spent to avoid the whole &quot;Parchment Lottery&quot; where you turn in and hope.<br>
<br>
There was also a representative from one of the bigger guilds on the server wandering tier 1 PoP zones this weekend auctioning to sell spells.  He supposedly had &quot;every wizard spell, every mage spell but 61 and 63 pets, and most enchanter spells&quot;.  His price for the 65 earth pet was 40k.  Of course, this individual is known as one of the biggest A'holes on the server, so he could have just been messing with folks.<br>
<br>
Personally, I don't have a big problem with the current system.  I only have 2 spells other than FoT right now (the purchased pet and focus choker from a parchment), but I have witnessed quite a few parchments drop.  All of the parchments I have had a shot at were from single xp groups, some with a necro as main/only healer.<br>
<br>
At first I was ticked off and depressed at the prospect of acquiring all of my spells.   But, the more I thought about it the more reasonable it seems.  After all, who says we are entitled to our spells as soon as we level?  The fact that there are things currently just out of my reach that ARE attainable with a little luck or work is what keeps this game going for me.  The fact that you have to complete trials to progress on to tier 2 or 3 zones for some of the spells is also a good thing, in my opinion. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=103898" target="top">Baron Evelle Fyrestrike</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
